</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="748C08FAFF8F500637A893B0073A97B2" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3C295B71FF8F500637A893B002989726" blockId="1.[151,1436,2005,2033]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,152,1511]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8F500537A893B0024791C9" bold="true" box="[151,274,2005,2032]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lateral oral margins not produced. Scutellum with large size calcars. Propleuron pilose. Basotarsomere of legs about 2 times as wide as apex of tibiae. Postero-apical corner of cell r 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C500634D694CF07569681" attach="left" box="[1001,1027,170,184]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4+5</subScript>
rounded. Apical crossvein M 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C5006327694CF06049681" attach="left" box="[1353,1361,170,184]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">1</subScript>
with a small inward appendix extending into cell r 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C5006354794AB01C796E5" attach="left" box="[632,658,206,220]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
4+ 
<quantity id="FB6EF694FF8C500635B594AB01C796E5" box="[650,658,206,220]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="5.0">5</quantity>
</subScript>
in some specimens (
<figureCitation id="A4AD47F4FF8C5006344794D9008496EE" box="[888,977,188,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1193,1218]" captionTargetBox="[162,1432,178,1170]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,174,1174]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microdon dentigiganteum Tian, Huo et Zhang, sp. nov. (A) Male head, lateral view; (B) Male head, dorsal view; (C) Female head, frontal view; (D) Female head, dorsal view; (E) Male scutellum; (F) Male antenna, dorsal view; (G) Wing; (H) Apex part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586844" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3586844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
). Length ratio of terga III:IV is about 1:2. Aedeagus projecting conspicuously beyond apex of hypandrium, furcate close to base, with dorsal process slightly longer than ventral process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C295B71FF8C500637F8954D073A97B2" blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1511]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
This species keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="FB9620F2FF8C500636E9954D0015977A" authority="Yano, 1915" authorityName="Yano" authorityYear="1915" box="[470,832,296,323]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500636E9954D01ED977B" box="[470,696,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Microdon japonicus</emphasis>
Yano, 
<quantity id="FB6EF694FF8C50063437954D0015977A" box="[776,832,296,323]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8641" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" unit="in" value="1915.0">1915</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the keys of 
<bibRefCitation id="58072680FF8C500634DD954D0662977A" author="Hironaga, T. &amp; Maruyama, M." box="[994,1335,296,323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" pagination="87 - 103" refId="ref5821" refString="Hironaga, T. &amp; Maruyama, M. (2004) The myrmecophilous hoverfly genus Microdon (Diptera, Syrphidae, Microdontinae) in Hokkaido, Japan, with descriptions of four new species. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, 30, 87 - 103." type="journal article" year="2004">Hironaga &amp; Maruyama (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="58072680FF8C50063253954C0271975E" author="Huo, K. - K. &amp; Ren, G. - D. &amp; Zheng, Z. - M." pageId="2" pageNumber="67" refId="ref5965" refString="Huo, K. - K., Ren, G. - D. &amp; Zheng, Z. - M. (2007) Fauna of Syrphidae from Mt. Qinling-Bashan in China (Insecta: Diptera). Chinese Agricultural Science and Technology Press, Beijing, 512 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Huo 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500637A89528039C975F" box="[151,201,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
. The new species can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="FB9620F2FF8C500635D1952800D4975F" authorityName="Yano" authorityYear="1915" box="[750,897,333,358]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500635D1952800D4975F" box="[750,897,333,358]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the entirely yellow pilose terga (partly black pilose in 
<taxonomicName id="FB9620F2FF8C500637C1951402C597B3" authorityName="Yano" authorityYear="1915" box="[254,400,369,394]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500637C1951402C597B3" box="[254,400,369,394]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the black tibiae (basal 2/3 yellowish white in 
<taxonomicName id="FB9620F2FF8C500634F39514070A97B3" authorityName="Yano" authorityYear="1915" box="[972,1119,369,394]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500634F39514070A97B3" box="[972,1119,369,394]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">M. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="748C08FAFF8C500637F895F102509336" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph id="3C295B71FF8C500637F895F10671929B" blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1511]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500637F895F1024E9796" bold="true" box="[199,283,404,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">MALE</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="E32DE5D3FF8C5006361595F102CC9796" box="[298,409,404,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Holotype</typeStatus>
). Body length: 
<quantity id="FB6EF694FF8C5006357C95F001DB9796" box="[579,654,405,431]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="12.0">12mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500635A695F0018C9796" bold="true" box="[665,729,405,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Head</emphasis>
: Roughly oval in frontal view (
<figureCitation id="A4AD47F4FF8C5006330695F107C49796" box="[1081,1169,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1916,1941]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,199,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,174,1896]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Microdon dentigiganteum Tian, Huo et Zhang, sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Habitus, dorsal view; (B) Habitus, lateral view; (C) Abdomen; (D) Anepisternum. Scale bars: a, b, c = 5mm; d = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3586842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
), almost as wide as mesonotum. Eyes bare. Vertex and frons shining black, yellow pilose, the width of the vertex at the posterior margin of eyes is about 34% of head width. Eye margins converging at level of frons (
<figureCitation id="A4AD47F4FF8C5006333C95B9070F97CE" box="[1027,1114,476,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1193,1218]" captionTargetBox="[162,1432,178,1170]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,174,1174]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Microdon dentigiganteum Tian, Huo et Zhang, sp. nov. (A) Male head, lateral view; (B) Male head, dorsal view; (C) Female head, frontal view; (D) Female head, dorsal view; (E) Male scutellum; (F) Male antenna, dorsal view; (G) Wing; (H) Apex part of wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586844" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3586844/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), with mutual distance about 57% width of posterior margin of vertex. Occiput widened, black, yellowish pilose, with gray white pollinosity. Face almost straight in profile; about equal to the width of the posterior margin of vertex; shining black and punctate, long yellowish pilose. Lateral oral margins not produced. Gena black, yellowish pilose. Antennal pits about as wide as high. Antenna black; antennal ratio approximately 4.8: 1: 4.2; arista bare, yellow, about as long as the basoflagellomere. 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C5006360B96F402D89492" bold="true" box="[308,397,657,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Thorax</emphasis>
: Scutum shining black with green hues, punctate, yellowish pilose. Scutellum dark orange, except anterior margin which is widely black with green hues; yellowish pilose; with deeply concave posterior margin; with huge posterolateral calcars conspicuously longer than 1/2 of the scutellum length. Pleuron shining black with green hues, punctate; all pile yellow.Anepisternum (
<figureCitation id="A4AD47F4FF8C5006342C9699003C952E" box="[787,873,764,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1916,1941]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,199,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,174,1896]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Microdon dentigiganteum Tian, Huo et Zhang, sp. nov., male holotype. (A) Habitus, dorsal view; (B) Habitus, lateral view; (C) Abdomen; (D) Anepisternum. Scale bars: a, b, c = 5mm; d = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3586842/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) pilose anteriorly and posterodorsally, with widely bare part in between, which nearly reaches anepisternum dorsally. Anepimeron pilose anteriorly. Katepisternum pilose posterodorsally; bare ventrally. Katatergum long yellowish-brown microtrichose. Metasternum yellow pilose. 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500637A8970D038D95BA" bold="true" box="[151,216,872,899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Wing</emphasis>
: Hyaline, vein yellow; microtrichose; vein R 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C500635ED971F01B995B1" attach="left" box="[722,748,890,904]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4+5</subScript>
with appendix; vein M 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C500634CF971F00AD95B1" attach="left" box="[1008,1016,890,904]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">1</subScript>
more and less straight, perpendicular to vein R 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C500637C397FB02439595" attach="left" box="[252,278,926,940]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4+5</subScript>
; postero-apical corner of cell r 
<subScript id="A0125934FF8C5006355397FB01D39595" attach="left" box="[620,646,926,940]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">4+5</subScript>
rounded, without appendix; crossvein r-m located basal 1/4 of cell dm. Calypter and halter yellow. 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500636F297D4015095F2" bold="true" box="[461,517,945,971]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Legs</emphasis>
: Black, except for dark brown tarsomeres 1–3 and brown tarsi 4–5; yellow pilose, except for brown pilose on tarsi. Tarsi are very wide and flat. 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C5006345D97B1008295D6" bold="true" box="[866,983,980,1007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Broadly oval, tapering, about 1.5× the width of thorax. Lateral margin of terga II–IV thickened and bent downward. Abdomen black, except posterior part of tergum IV and sternum IV which are more or less red-brown, with green hues, punctate, yellow pilose. Length ratio of terga II–IV about 1: 2: 4. 
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500636CB902501379262" bold="true" box="[500,610,1088,1115]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="A4AD47F4FF8C5006354E902501E39262" box="[625,694,1088,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1304,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1304,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia of Microdon dentigiganteum Tian, Huo et Zhang, sp. nov.. (A) lateral view; (B) ventral view. Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; aed apod, aedeagal apodeme; cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3586846/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
): Aedeagus projecting conspicuously beyond apex of hypandrium, furcate near its base, with dorsal process slightly longer than ventral process; surstylus knife-shaped (lateral view), with a short and wide lobe at ventral margin (see 
<figureCitation id="A4AD47F4FF8C500635FF90ED0043929A" box="[704,790,1160,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1304,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,1304,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia of Microdon dentigiganteum Tian, Huo et Zhang, sp. nov.. (A) lateral view; (B) ventral view. Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; aed apod, aedeagal apodeme; cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; hypd, hypandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3586846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3586846/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
, arrows), punctured; cercus roughly triangular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3C295B71FF8C500637F890C902509336" blockId="2.[151,1437,152,1511]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500637F890C9026A92FE" bold="true" box="[199,319,1196,1223]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">FEMALE</emphasis>
. Body length: 
<quantity id="FB6EF694FF8C500636D790C8016692FE" box="[488,563,1197,1223]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="14.0">14mm</quantity>
. Similar to male, except for the following differences: Face equal to width of frons and vertex, occupying about 40% of head width in frontal view. Length of tergum IV approximately equal to tergum V.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
